## Common anti-patterns

| Anti-pattern | Why it's wrong |
|---|---|
| Defaulting to SPA for content sites | SEO suffers; TTFB is worst; no SSG benefit |
| Server data in global client state (Redux/Zustand) | Re-implements caching badly; use TanStack Query / SWR / Pinia query |
| `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` / `v-html` with user input | XSS; sanitize or render as text |
| Lighthouse-only perf measurement | Lab numbers do not equal real users; need RUM |
| One giant `_app.tsx` / `App.vue` with all providers | Hard to refactor; per-route providers when scope is per-route |
| Visual regression on every component | Brittle; PR noise; opt-in per-component when actually needed |
| Disabling `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps` to silence warnings | Hides real bugs; fix the dep array or memo properly |
| `tsconfig.strict: false` for "speed" | The bugs you save now you will find at 3am |
| Inline event handlers in heavy lists | Re-allocates per render; ok for leaves, problem for virtualized rows |
| No CSP header | Inline-script XSS; CDN compromise propagates |
| Secrets in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` / `VITE_*` | Baked into the bundle; visible to every user |
| `npm install` (vs `npm ci`) in CI | Lockfile bypass; non-reproducible builds |

